<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[‘A gorgeous sight’: delight and wonder as US viewers watch annular solar eclipse]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/oct/14/annular-solar-eclipse-nasa-new-mexico]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T18:51:49Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/d095fcf7fb9847bd811065028f546e0f5206abad/0_0_2400_1440 /master/2400.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=228c02cbc598eb8ed3c5e8a26aae10c9&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;云层中深灰色的天空中的一条白色，树木或灌木丛中的带刺树枝模糊不清&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;这是 16 年来不会再发生的时刻 - 大自然在某些地方遮盖了它。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“今天科珀斯克里斯蒂本来应该是阳光明媚的现在到处都是云。试图看看我们必须开车去哪里，”德克萨斯州一位沮丧的日食观看者在 2024 年日全食&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/groups/eclipse2024&quot;>;Facebook 页面&lt;/a>;上发帖。 （标题提到了明年四月的日全食，在美国的某些地区可以看到。）&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在日食狭窄路径沿线的小镇和城市，人们既兴奋又担心天气，并担心他们会被蜂拥而至观看天体事件（也称为日环食）的游客淹没。在包括加利福尼亚州和俄勒冈州在内的一些西部州，云和雾可能会遮挡日食的视野。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;59fef478ff655b887d17e1a8feffcac17e2f6264&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim. co.uk/59fef478ff655b887d17e1a8feffcac17e2f6264/0_148_5577_3346/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;白人和棕色人种、成人、儿童和青少年，脖子向后伸，脸上戴眼镜&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;2023 年 10 月 14 日，德克萨斯州圣安东尼奥，观众使用特殊眼镜观看月亮在太阳前面移动。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Eric Gay/美联社&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;当日全食在俄勒冈州尤金开始时，日食只能时断时续地可见，太阳的光有时会从月亮后面透过云层探出，令人惊叹不已，还夹杂着失望的呻吟声。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://twitter.com/ChrisPietsch/status/1713252111948083235&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;我总是说幸运比好更好，但今天早上我自己创造了运气.&lt;br>;&lt;br>;仍然不敢相信我看到了。一直被云层覆盖，直到没有！ &lt;br>;&lt;br>;有关俄勒冈州周围日环食的更多信息，请访问 &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/4aFBEc3229&quot;>;https://t.co/4aFBEc3229&lt;/a>;&lt;a href=&quot;https ://twitter.com/hashtag/SolarEclipse2023?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;#SolarEclipse2023&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hashtag/SolarEclipse?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src =twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;#SolarEclipse&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/registerguard?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;@registerguard&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://t .co/JEAIZ2GAqx&quot;>;pic.twitter.com/JEAIZ2GAqx&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>;— Chris Pietsch (@ChrisPietsch) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ChrisPietsch/status/1713252111948083235?ref_src=twsrc %5Etfw&quot;>;2023 年 10 月 14 日&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;在德克萨斯州的其他地方，天气晴朗，孩子们在克尔维尔举行的一场热闹的观看派对上倒计时，直到月亮完全进入月亮的那一刻&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在新墨西哥州，天空清澈见底，让数以万计的观众一览无遗。由于日食恰逢国际气球嘉年华，吸引了近 100,000 名观众，数百个彩色热气球在清晨集体升空，因此他们得到了双重待遇。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;7ffc53c6a01f2358fd64b90f303919c110282bbb&quot;>; &lt; img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/7ffc53c6a01f2358fd64b90f303919c110282bbb/0_0_7536_4522/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;一个穿着粉红色寒冷天气装备的可爱婴儿位于画面中央，俯视头顶，她身后的天空点缀着热气球，其中一个看起来像一只戴着飞行员太阳镜的卡通花栗鼠。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;2023 年 10 月 13 日，新墨西哥州阿尔伯克基日食发生前，热气球升空，克拉丽莎被她的父亲升到空中。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Patrick T Fallon/AFP/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;周六早上，组织者分发了 80,000 副观看眼镜。随着环形成，热气球飞行员使用丙烷燃烧器向上喷射火焰，响起了叫喊声、叫喊声和尖叫声。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://twitter.com/jolinegkg/status/ 1713233264457228584&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hashtag/RingofFire?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;#RingofFire&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https: //twitter.com/hashtag/Eclipse?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;#Eclipse&lt;/a>; MT 10:28，新墨西哥州东山 &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/ LZikkgxaAL&quot;>;pic.twitter.com/LZikkgxaAL&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>;— Joline Gutierrez Krueger 🤦🏾‍♀️🖋🗒👩🏽‍💻📰🇺🇦 (@jolinegkg) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter. com/jolinegkg/status/1713233264457228584?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;2023 年 10 月 14 日&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;美国宇航局从阿尔伯克基直播了此次活动，记录了可以听到的喘息和欢呼声当达到环度时。 “我们处于环形之中。美国宇航局的太阳物理学家迈克尔·柯克 (Michael Kirk) 说：“这是一道绚丽的景象。”是今天日食的亮点。它只持续几分钟。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;26968bc248672d875aa3f6ae36d2acecc763e5ff&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/26968bc248672d875aa3f6ae36d2acecc763e5ff/0_122_8256_495 4/1000.jpg&quot; 替代“一张大部分是黑色的图像，天空中有一个明亮的白色光圈，你看到的是地面上有一圈热空气篮，每个篮子都向天空喷射火焰。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;2023 年 10 月 14 日，新墨西哥州阿尔伯克基发生日环食时，热气球操作员用燃烧器制造出一个“火环”。&lt;/span >; &lt;span>;摄影：Patrick T Fallon/AFP/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;科罗拉多州奥罗拉市的艾伦·哈恩 (Allan Hahn) 参加这个节日已经 34 年了，首先是作为一名工作人员，然后成为一名有执照的气球飞行员。他的气球“Heaven Bound Too”是在日食期间天空变暗时被选中进行特殊“发光”表演的 72 个气球之一。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“能够来到这里，将我们对飞行的热爱与像日食这样非常自然的事情，”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://twitter.com/Thiefainemagre/status/1713233180885758135&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;拍到了蚀。 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hashtag/eclipse?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;#eclipse&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hashtag/utah ?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;#utah&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/8jTPF8y5Rq&quot;>;pic.twitter.com/8jTPF8y5Rq&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>;— Thiefaine Magre (@Thiefainemagre) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Thiefainemagre/status/1713233180885758135?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;2023 年 10 月 14 日&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p >;这次天体活动将美国各地的日食观测者带到了该国的偏远角落，试图获得尽可能最好的视野。在犹他州南部的布莱斯峡谷国家公园，一条著名的小径蜿蜒穿过红岩不祥的山谷，日食爱好者在日出前来到这条小径，在沿途的角落和缝隙中标出他们最喜欢的地点，在这条小径上可以看到微弱的灯光。 .&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我只是认为这是将我们所有人团结在一起的事情之一，”癌症药物开发人员约翰·爱德华兹 (John Edwards) 说，他独自穿越全国，试图从布莱斯峡谷观看日食。 “我只是认为正是看到这些罕见的独特经历才让我来到这里。这种情况非常罕见。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 15 Oct 2023 03:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Ireland v New Zealand: Rugby World Cup 2023 quarter-final – live]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2023/oct/14/ireland-v-new-zealand-rugby-world-cup-2023-quarter-final-live-score-updates]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T18:21:56Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/67a150e4616536b6431255e671a458f192c33d94/0_11_5966_3580 /master/5966.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=c7b0eb48bbaacd22b0e5e8d1629e3d82&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;爱尔兰队在比赛前在看台上欢呼。&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 15 Oct 2023 02:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Sheikh Jassim pulls out of race to buy Manchester United from Glazers]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/oct/14/sheikh-jassim-pulls-out-of-race-to-buy-manchester-united-from-glazers]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T17:43:35Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ef31383a8ab7aa63af703eda96e76e59a9b3f987/43_0_1200_720 /master/1200.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=76b5513f6b680089900844ed6f2d46ec&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Sheikh Jassim bin Hamad al-Thani&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Sheikh Jassim bin Hamad al-Thani 被认为是已经不再有兴趣从格雷泽家族手中收购曼联。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这位卡塔尔亿万富翁告诉这个来自佛罗里达的家族，他自 2005 年以来一直拥有曼联，并自 4 月以来一直在寻求收购该俱乐部的报价。退出进程。谢赫·贾西姆的兴趣是购买俱乐部 100% 的股份，但据消息人士透露，在格雷泽家族提出了一个“异想天开且古怪”的要价后，他不会再进一步​​追求这一目标。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;吉姆·拉特克利夫爵士曼彻斯特出生的英力士化工亿万富翁是卡塔尔银行家在俱乐部的主要竞争对手，最近与 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/sep/26/sir-jim -ratcliffe-to-restruct-his-bid-to-buy-manchester-unit-after-concerns&quot;>;只购买曼联的一部分&lt;/a>;，而不是全部买断。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当前市场曼联的估值为 32 亿美元，但据悉谢赫·贾西姆的出价是这个数字的两倍，结果被格雷泽家族拒绝了。他承诺全额现金出价，以消除俱乐部 9 月份财务业绩中报告的 10 亿英镑债务，并翻新或更换现已过时的老特拉福德球场。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-atom-id =&quot;eab35d41-dbe9-4aec-9209-ae22c3b80688&quot; data-atom-type=&quot;guide&quot;>; &lt;详细信息 data-snippet-id=&quot;eab35d41-dbe9-4aec-9209-ae22c3b80688&quot; data-snippet-type=&quot;guide&quot; >; &lt;summary>; &lt;span>;快速指南&lt;/span>; &lt;h4>;如何注册体育突发新闻提醒？&lt;/h4>;&lt;span aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot;>; &lt;span>; &lt;svg width=&quot;18px &quot; height=&quot;18px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 18 18&quot;>; &lt;路径 d=&quot;M8.2 0h1.6l.4 7.8 7.8.4v1.6l-7.8.4-.4 7.8H8.2l-.4-7.8 L0 9.8V8.2l7.8-.4.4-7.8z&quot; />; &lt;/svg>; 显示&lt;/span>; &lt;span>; &lt;svg width=&quot;32px&quot; height=&quot;32px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 32 32&quot;>; &lt; rect x=&quot;5&quot; y=&quot;15&quot; width=&quot;22&quot; height=&quot;3&quot;>;&lt;/rect>; &lt;/svg>; 隐藏&lt;/span>; &lt;/span>; &lt;/summary>; &lt;div>; &lt;div>; &lt; ul>; &lt;li>;通过搜索“The Guardian”从 iPhone 上的 iOS App Store 或 Android 上的 Google Play 商店下载 Guardian 应用。&lt;/li>; &lt;li>;如果您已经安装了 Guardian 应用，请确保您“请使用最新版本。&lt;/li>; &lt;li>;在 Guardian 应用中，点击右下角的“菜单”按钮，然后依次转到“设置”（齿轮图标）和“通知”。&lt;/li>; &lt;li>;打开体育通知。&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/div>; &lt;footer>; &lt;div>; &lt;div>; 这有帮助吗？ &lt;/div>;&lt;button value=&quot;like&quot; aria-label=&quot;Yes&quot;>; &lt;svg width=&quot;40px&quot; height=&quot;40px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 40 40&quot;>; &lt;path fill=&quot;#FFF&quot; d= “M33.78 22.437l-4.228 13.98L27.93 37.5 5.062 34.14V15.503l7.8-1.517L24.354 2.5h1.624L28.9 5.426l-4.548 8.67h.107l10.477 1. 31&quot; />; &lt;/svg>;&lt; /button>; &lt;button value=&quot;不喜欢&quot; aria-label=&quot;否&quot;>; &lt;svg width=&quot;40px&quot; height=&quot;40px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 40 40&quot;>; &lt;path fill=&quot;#FFF&quot; d=&quot; M33.78 22.437l-4.228 13.98L27.93 37.5 5.062 34.14V15.503l7.8-1.517L24.354 2.5h1.624L28.9 5.426l-4.548 8.67h.107l10.477 1.3 1&quot; />; &lt;/svg>;&lt;/按钮>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div hide aria-role=&quot;alert&quot; aria-live=&quot;polite&quot;>; 感谢您的反馈。 &lt;/div>; &lt;/footer>; &lt;/details>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;更多详细信息请关注...&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 15 Oct 2023 02:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Ring of fire’ visible in parts of US as crowds gathered to watch annular eclipse]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/oct/14/ring-fire-eclipse-visible-states-us]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T17:25:21Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/b0c3b2c3e11d4293062d12767fc43562d92aaf14/0_0_5255_3155 /master/5255.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=cce6bc08570f14b7d556858a3cbab61c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;一个大约 5 岁的白人男孩用双手举着黑色软太阳镜，凝视着天空&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;当“日环时刻”到来时，人们纷纷拍照，人群欢呼，天空变暗——至少在可以看到日环食的区域是这样。&lt;/p>; &lt;日食期间的环度是指月亮完全位于太阳前面的时刻，形成火环，这是今天日食的视觉亮点。它只持续几分钟。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;日食的直接路径覆盖了从俄勒冈州到德克萨斯州的八个州的部分地区，尽管至少是日偏食，减去火环，&lt;a href=&quot;https ://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/oct/11/where-watch-eclipse-ring-fire&quot;>;在包括阿拉斯加在内的所有其他 41 个大陆州都可见&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p >; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/oct/13/what-is-annular-solar-eclipse-where -will-ring-of-fire-be-visible&quot;>;什么是日环食以及“火环”在哪里可见？&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;美国宇航局跟上&lt;a href=&quot;https://science.nasa.gov/eclipses/future-eclipses/eclipse-2023/2023-annular-eclipse-broadcast/&quot;>;活动直播&lt;/a>;，包括望远镜看到的景色在它的轨道上。当航天局正在观看的新墨西哥州阿尔伯克基&lt;a href=&quot;https://x.com/NASA/status/1713232586590330923?s=20&quot;>;达到环度&lt;/a>;时，可以听到喘息声和欢呼声日食。 “我们处于环形之中。这是一个美丽的景象，”美国宇航局的太阳物理学家迈克尔·柯克说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;23491ce0dc5f619f1019d4c7491e51cc48786d81&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk /23491ce0dc5f619f1019d4c7491e51cc48786d81/0_80_3073_1844/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;全黑图像，中间有一个完美的圆形细圆圈。你不会知道这不是图形图像。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;2023 年 10 月 14 日在新墨西哥州阿尔伯克基看到的月亮完全穿过太阳的前面。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Sam Wasson /Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;日环食是指月球经过太阳和地球之间，但位于或接近其距地球最远点的情况。它看起来比太阳小，并且没有完全覆盖太阳，在一个更大、更亮的圆盘上产生一个黑色圆盘的图像，并在月球周围产生一个火环的效果。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在偏远的角落在这个国家，日食观察者们起得很早，或者露营过夜，试图获得尽可能最好的视野。在犹他州南部的布莱斯峡谷国家公园，日出前沿着一条著名的小径可以看到灯光，这条小径蜿蜒穿过红岩不祥的山谷。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我只是认为这是将我们所有人团结在一起的事情之一”，癌症药物开发商约翰·爱德华兹（John Edwards）独自一人穿越全国，试图从布莱斯峡谷观看日食。 “正是看到这些罕见的独特经历才让我来到这里。这几乎是罕见的。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;北美最近一次可见的日环食是在 2012 年。下一次观看日环食的机会将是 2039 年在阿拉斯加，以及 2046 年在美国本土 48 个州。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;全国各地的众多天文馆、科学博物馆、学校和其他场所正在举办日食节和观看派对。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;美国宇航局敦促 &lt;a href=&quot;https://science .nasa.gov/eclipses/future-eclipses/eclipse-2023/safety/&quot;>;安全第一的方法&lt;/a>;，警告人们不要观看事件，除非通过特殊的日食眼镜、太阳观察器或太阳滤光片望远镜。航天局推荐替代的非直接观察方法，例如针孔投影仪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;科学家们还利用这个机会研究阳光突然下降如何影响高层大气。美国宇航局的三枚“探空火箭”是 &lt;a href=&quot;https://science.nasa.gov/solar-system/skywatching/eclipses/solar-eclipses/2023-solar-eclipse/to-study-atmosphere-nasa-rockets- will-fly-into-oct-eclipses-shadow/&quot;>;从新墨西哥州的白沙导弹靶场发射到日食的阴影&lt;/a>;，以记录大气变化。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;经过较早的一次通过后在阿拉斯加上空，从太平洋时间上午 9.13 左右开始，俄勒冈州中部和南部可以看到日环食，并沿着东南路径穿过加利福尼亚州、内华达州、爱达荷州、犹他州、亚利桑那州和新墨西哥州的部分地区，然后穿过德克萨斯州的大片地区并进入墨西哥湾。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尤卡坦半岛以及从伯利兹到巴西的几个中美洲和南美洲国家也位于环形路径上。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;美联社为这个故事做出了贡献&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 15 Oct 2023 01:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Argentina reach World Cup semi-final after fighting back to defeat Wales]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/oct/14/wales-argentina-rugby-world-cup-quarter-final-match-report]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T17:10:55Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/46647925377841d43a6bd9e798713eed414ce153/0_176_7224_4334 /master/7224.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=fdf8e5156ce6f8440e9f41136310695e&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;尼古拉斯·桑切斯在阿根廷对阵威尔士的第二次尝试中扑救&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;威尔士被橄榄球世界淘汰埃米利亚诺·博菲利 (Emiliano Boffelli) 带领阿根廷队在杯赛结束后发起反击，最终在韦洛德罗姆球场 (Stade Vélodrome) 以 29-17 赢得了一场激动人心的比赛。沃伦·加特兰 (Warren Gatland) 的球队在过去四场比赛中第三次进入世界杯半决赛寄予厚望，但阿根廷队在艰难晋级后撕毁了成绩单。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;威尔士队以 10-0 领先，最终以 10-0 领先。丹·比格 (Dan Biggar) 尝试、转换和点球，结果博菲利 (Boffelli) 在半场两边的破坏性咒语中以四个点球消除了赤字。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt; a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2023/oct/14/wales-v-argentina-rugby-world-cup-quarter-final-live-score-updates&quot;>;威尔士 v 阿根廷：2023 年橄榄球世界杯四分之一决赛 - 直播&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;半场托莫斯·威廉姆斯 (Tomos Williams) 的射门再次被比格 (Biggar) 射门，让威尔士重新领先。但美洲狮队的后援乔尔·斯克拉维（Joel Sclavi）落地，替补前卫尼古拉斯·桑切斯（Nicolás Sánchez）在最后几秒声称拦截尝试。博菲利两罚全中，然后桑切斯在最后一刻主罚点球。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这一切都在威尔士的伤口上撒了盐，尽管美洲狮很幸运地看到锁定吉多·佩蒂（Guido Petti）避免因肩部撞击而受到制裁。威尔士中锋尼克·汤普金斯 (Nick Tompkins) 在距离比赛结束还有 16 分钟时被罚下。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;裁判卡尔·迪克森 (Karl Dickson) 接替了受伤的雅科·佩珀 (Jaco Peyper)，但在电视比赛正式咨询后没有判罚任何牌，威尔士球员显得很困惑。威尔士队的失利意味着比格国家队生涯的结束，他在八月份宣布将在世界杯后退出测试赛场。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿根廷队在小组出线中付出了很大的努力，但他们取得了良好的开局通过扩展威尔士的防守，在完美的条件下。不过，博菲利错失了 30 米外的点球机会，威尔士队凭借自己的流畅性和决心将多产的射门得分手路易斯·里斯-扎米特释放到太空中。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;威尔士队在 14 分钟后打破了僵局。当中锋乔治·诺斯（George North）参加威尔士创纪录的第四次世界杯四分之一决赛时，在比格（Biggar）穿过门柱之间并完成自己的尝试之前取得了初步进展。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;佩珀（Peyper）随后离开了比赛，似乎受到了小腿的伤害肌肉受伤，迪克森吹响了哨子。威尔士的球衣也存在问题，几名球员看到背后的号码脱落，随后比格通过远射点球恢复了一定程度的平静，将比分改写为 10-0。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id= &quot;51a12de190af54e600ce43910ac5ad0c91bf1985&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/51a12de190af54e600ce43910ac5ad0c91bf1985/0_29_3500_2100/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;路易斯·里斯-在威尔士输给阿根廷的比赛中，扎米特的球衣号码掉了下来&quot; width=&quot;1000 &quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;路易斯·里斯·扎米特 (Louis Rees-Zammit) 的球衣号码在威尔士输给阿根廷的比赛中掉落。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Mike Egerton/PA&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/图>; &lt;p>;当比格在铲倒圣地亚哥·乔科巴雷斯后捂着胸口倒地时，威尔士队伍中弥漫着焦虑，但他在治疗后很快恢复了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;威尔士的问题在于争边球，他们自己输掉了两场比赛开场25分钟内罚球，但阿根廷未能占据优势，美洲狮队在令人印象深刻的开局后几乎没有取得进展。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;比格随后错失点球，但博菲利在上半场结束时连续踢球更加准确阿根廷队进攻不断，信心不断增强，直到加时赛爆发，美洲狮队仅以 10-6 落后。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在博菲利第二次成功进球之前，威尔士边锋乔什·亚当斯幸运地避免了黄牌。由于推倒了一名无球的阿根廷球员，半场结束时，胡克·德维·莱克 (Dewi Lake) 换下瑞安·埃利亚斯 (Ryan Elias)。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;半场结束后，阿根廷队保持主动，博菲利完成了快速点球帽子戏法，向暂时迷失方向的威尔士队发出进一步的警告信号。但没有人能阻止博菲利，他在本方半场内两米处主罚点球，首次让威尔士队落后。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;托莫斯·威廉姆斯 (Tomos Williams) 接替加雷斯·戴维斯 (Gareth Davies) 后立即发挥作用，打破了阿根廷队的大门。 25 米的迂回跑动中防守。比格的转换让威尔士重新领先，在接近小时标记时领先五分。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-atom-id=&quot;eab35d41-dbe9-4aec-9209-ae22c3b80688&quot; data-atom-type=&quot;guide &quot;>; &lt;details data-snippet-id=&quot;eab35d41-dbe9-4aec-9209-ae22c3b80688&quot; data-snippet-type=&quot;guide&quot;>; &lt;summary>; &lt;span>;快速指南&lt;/span>; &lt;h4>;如何签名准备接收体育突发新闻提醒吗？&lt;/h4>;&lt;span aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot;>; &lt;span>; &lt;svg width=&quot;18px&quot; height=&quot;18px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 18 18&quot;>; &lt;path d=&quot; M8.2 0h1.6l.4 7.8 7.8.4v1.6l-7.8.4-.4 7.8H8.2l-.4-7.8L0 9.8V8.2l7.8-.4.4-7.8z&quot; />; &lt;/svg>;显示&lt;/span>; &lt;span>; &lt;svg width=&quot;32px&quot; height=&quot;32px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 32 32&quot;>; &lt;rect x=&quot;5&quot; y=&quot;15&quot; width=&quot;22&quot; height=&quot;3 &quot;>;&lt;/rect>; &lt;/svg>; 隐藏&lt;/span>; &lt;/span>; &lt;/summary>; &lt;div>; &lt;div>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>;从 iPhone 上的 iOS App Store 或 Google Play 下载 Guardian 应用通过搜索“The Guardian”在 Android 上存储。&lt;/li>; &lt;li>;如果您已有 Guardian 应用，请确保您使用的是最新版本。&lt;/li>; &lt;li>;在 Guardian 应用中，点按点击右下角的“菜单”按钮，然后转到“设置”（齿轮图标），然后转到“通知”。&lt;/li>; &lt;li>;打开运动通知。&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/div>; &lt; footer>; &lt;div>; &lt;div>; 这有帮助吗？ &lt;/div>;&lt;button value=&quot;like&quot; aria-label=&quot;Yes&quot;>; &lt;svg width=&quot;40px&quot; height=&quot;40px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 40 40&quot;>; &lt;path fill=&quot;#FFF&quot; d= “M33.78 22.437l-4.228 13.98L27.93 37.5 5.062 34.14V15.503l7.8-1.517L24.354 2.5h1.624L28.9 5.426l-4.548 8.67h.107l10.477 1. 31&quot; />; &lt;/svg>;&lt; /button>; &lt;button value=&quot;不喜欢&quot; aria-label=&quot;否&quot;>; &lt;svg width=&quot;40px&quot; height=&quot;40px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 40 40&quot;>; &lt;path fill=&quot;#FFF&quot; d=&quot; M33.78 22.437l-4.228 13.98L27.93 37.5 5.062 34.14V15.503l7.8-1.517L24.354 2.5h1.624L28.9 5.426l-4.548 8.67h.107l10.477 1.3 1&quot; />; &lt;/svg>;&lt;/按钮>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div hide aria-role=&quot;alert&quot; aria-live=&quot;polite&quot;>; 感谢您的反馈。 &lt;/div>; &lt;/footer>; &lt;/details>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;佩蒂放手后，斯克拉维持续施压，随后博菲利的转换让阿根廷重新领先，威尔士再次陷入困境。但加特兰的球队在最后阶段向阿根廷队倾注了一切，里斯-扎米特在角球中拼命接近射门。桑切斯拦截萨姆·科斯特洛的传球，博菲利完成射门，桑切斯主罚点球，威尔士出局。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;接下来是罗伯特·基特森的报告。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 15 Oct 2023 01:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[DUP making ‘progress’ in post-Brexit trade talks, says Donaldson]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/oct/14/dup-making-progress-in-post-brexit-trade-talks-says-donaldson]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T15:42:21Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c5163b97a397d97f911baa20b2890b9fcd736895/0_134_3500_2101 /master/3500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=9833a6f77fbb0138f4e20f4e750240b1&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;杰弗里·唐纳森爵士在其政党年度会议期间发表主题演讲&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;民主统一党 ( DUP）正在与英国政府就脱欧后贸易安排进行谈判取得“进展”，但该党不会在 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/杰弗里·唐纳森 (Jeffrey Donaldson) 表示，除非北爱尔兰的根本问题得到解决，否则北爱尔兰&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;北爱尔兰民主统一党 (DUP) 领导人周六在贝尔法斯特举行的党内会议上表示，他希望恢复权力下放北爱尔兰政府，但“不会害怕对他认为不充分的任何协议说不”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“新安排必须能够获得工会主义者和民族主义者的支持。工会主义者的权利不能被削弱、边缘化或以不如民族主义者重要的方式对待。如果我们要建设我们所渴望的真正共同的未来，就必须恢复这些平衡，并尊重和保护我们的权利。”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;英国和爱尔兰政府以及其他北爱尔兰政党进行了审查演讲中寻找有关唐纳森是否可能试图向其政党出售潜在交易或继续抵制斯托蒙特行政和议会的迹象，自去年民主统一党退出以来，斯托蒙特行政和议会一直处于封存状态。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;党和政府官员我们已经讨论了几个月，看看&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/feb/27/the-guardian-view-on-the-windsor-framework-faceing-up- to-the-brexit-mess&quot;>;温莎框架&lt;/a>;重新制定了北爱尔兰协议，可以缓解民主统一党对北爱尔兰在英国地位的担忧。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该党面临着来自伦敦的压力，都柏林和其他政党结束日益恶化的政治真空 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/oct/13/the-hope-we-had-is-gone-how -20-months-of-stasis-has-paralysed-northern-ireland&quot;>;公共服务危机&lt;/a>;，这可能导致唐宁街在爱尔兰政府的投入下实施来自伦敦的直接统治。&lt;/p >; &lt;p>;唐纳森表示，温莎框架代表了进步，但没有解决根本问题。不过，他也表达了结束僵局的愿望。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“如果我们想为工会做出积极的贡献，那么拥有能够成功为北爱尔兰每个人提供服务的当地机构是建立联盟的一个重要因素。我们的案例。对于那些认为直接统治是更好选择的人，我要说的是：威斯敏斯特一次又一次地向我们强加与北爱尔兰人民的需求或愿望不符的法律。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六早些时候，DUP 副党魁 Gavin Robinson 表示，与伦敦达成的任何协议都需要逆转 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/oct/13/northern-ireland -four-key-areas-in-crisis&quot;>;预算削减&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“北爱尔兰得到的比它需要的要少，”他说。 “如果我们想要一个能够为人民提供服务的政府，就需要财力。就目前情况而言，财政部现在正在惩罚北爱尔兰的资金不足。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;新芬党第一任部长候任人米歇尔·奥尼尔 (Michelle O&#39;Neill) 指责民主统一党 (DUP) 长期处于停滞状态。 “在没有人开车的情况下，当人们痛苦地躺在等待治疗和手术的情况下，这种漂流不能再持续一个月了。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 15 Oct 2023 00:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘It was a plague’: Killarney becomes first Irish town to ban single-use coffee cups]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/14/it-was-a-plague-killarney-becomes-first-irish-town-to-ban-single-use-coffee-cups]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T14:00:00Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/e010d2cfb8dc982f301fcf825369d1a427537197/0_200_6000_3600 /master/6000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=91b6ab30b1986d0f2533cdf19bff27b4&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;凯里郡基拉尼的学院街&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;基拉尼曾经接受它作为成为的代价旅游小镇：无处不在 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/apr/26/why-britains-25-billion-paper-coffee-cups-are-an-eco-disaster&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;一次性咖啡杯&lt;/a>;从垃圾箱中溢出，在道路上乱扔垃圾，污染了&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jun/16/ireland-killarney-national- Park-battles-ecological-calamity&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;该地区的国家公园&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;凯里郡镇每周喝掉约 23,000 杯咖啡 - 每年超过 100 万杯 - 总计18.5 吨废物。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;不再是了。三个月前，基拉尼成为&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/ireland&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;爱尔兰&lt;/a>;第一个&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2022/dec/13/single-use- Plastic-items-to-be-banned-in-england-reports&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;逐步淘汰一次性咖啡杯&lt;/a>;。如果您想从咖啡馆或酒店购买外卖咖啡，则必须自带杯子或支付 2 欧元押金&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2016/sep/29/switch- disposable-coffee-cups-for-reusables-urge-campaign-groups&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;可重复使用的杯子&lt;/a>;，当杯子被归还时，它也会被归还。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;结果显而易见垃圾箱现在很少溢出，在街道和森林小路上也很少看到被遗弃的杯子。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这对城镇和乡村来说是一场瘟疫，”基拉尼组织主席迈克尔·格里森 (Michael Gleeson) 说看起来不错，这促进了公民的进步。 “这是一项美妙且必要的举措。散落在各处的杯子数量大大减少了。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在通往科克的 N22 公路的一段路段上，格里森曾经捡起五六个杯子，现在他往往只找到一个（如果有的话）。&lt;格里森说，包括特拉利和丁格尔在内的其他凯里城镇正在考虑效仿该实验，并希望该实验能够扩展到爱尔兰及其他地区。 “我们面临的巨大挑战是让我们的世界变得更加美丽。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;36e9fc03a09c326b05bdecf217ce819db1aec808&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/36e9fc03a09c326b05bdecf217ce819db1aec808/0_90_201 6_1210/ 1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;终止使用一次性咖啡杯的标志迎接基拉尼的游客。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;停止使用一次性咖啡杯的标志迎接基拉尼的游客。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Rory Carroll/The Guardian&lt;/ span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;消除一次性杯子听起来是一个相对温和的目​​标，但只有少数其他城镇，例如 &lt;a href=&quot;https://zerowasteeurope.eu/wp-content/据了解，德国的 uploads/2018/09/FreiburgCupfinal.pdf&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;弗莱堡&lt;/a>;也尝试过类似的举措。基拉尼竞选活动背后的人们知道原因 - 这并不容易。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们正在寻找社区项目的选择，我们想，‘哦，咖啡杯，那会很快’，”路易丝·伯恩 (Louise Byrne) 说基拉尼公园酒店和罗斯酒店的可持续发展经理。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“哦，我们错了，”另一位酒店经理 Ciara Treacy 说。 “这需要大量的工作，而且不会停止。人们认为我们是咖啡杯警察。不是。我们有工作。”特里西说，其他地方的试点项目步履蹒跚，因为参与的咖啡馆发现顾客转向继续提供一次性杯子的咖啡馆。 “一旦你给消费者选择的那一刻，他们就会享受到便利。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;1289898f99e6c26ba4f26c9f77acc56b740e0270&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/ 1289898f99e6c26ba4f26c9f77acc56b740e0270/0_151_2016_1210/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Louise Byrne, left, Ciara Treacy and Killian Treacy have led Killarney&#39;s scheme against single-use coffee cups.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Louise Byrne, left, Ciara Treacy and Killian Treacy have led Killarney&#39;s scheme against single-use coffee cups.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Rory Carroll/The Guardian&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;The campaign sought to enlist all of Killarney&#39;s 21 independent cafes, a lengthy process of individual face-to-face meetings, research, negotiations, a town hall-style gathering, a video, and more discussions.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In addition to environmental benefits, the organisers said cafes could save money – each disposable cup costs 20 to 30 cents – and enhance Killarney&#39;s brand.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Still, some cafe owners worried about forfeiting their stocks of single-use cups and alienating local customers as well as tourists. Eventually, nearly all signed up, and a credit union donated €5,000 for marketing, paving the way to the launch on 31 July. “If it can be done in Killarney, at the height of the tourist season, it can be done anywhere,” said Killian Treacy, of Luna Deli + Wine.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;More than 50 local businesses are now on board, including a factory that told staff to bring only reusable cups to work.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It&#39;s a great idea,” said Paul McClure, 43, visiting from San Diego. He had no objection to paying a €2 deposit for a takeaway cup that could be returned to any cafe in Killarney or 400 locations across Ireland, including Dublin airport, that are part of a wider campaign.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Thorunn Einarsdottir, sipping a flat white, said the scheme could work in her native Iceland. “It&#39;s really smart. It&#39;s like learning to organise your trash – it&#39;s habit.”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;3f55c0c1341006da0ae797301e1eff19642bcfbf&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/3f55c0c1341006da0ae797301e1eff19642bcfbf/0_38_2016_1210/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Thorunn Einarsdottir, who has moved to Killarney from Iceland, supports the elimination of single-use coffee cups.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Thorunn Einarsdottir, who has moved to Killarney from Iceland, supports the elimination of single-use coffee cups.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Rory Carroll/The Guardian&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Replicating the scheme in cities would require government intervention because not every cafe would voluntarily sign up, said Killian Treacy. The Irish government&#39;s planned 20-cent tax on disposable coffee cups, known as the latte levy, is a start, but not enough, he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Killarney cannot take success for granted – businesses need regular reassurance and updates, said Ciara Treacy. “There is a lot of hand-holding.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;At least one holdout remains. “We have a big stock of disposable cups to use up,” said Elaine Leahy of Noelle&#39;s cafe, which has stayed out of the scheme. That has had a knock-on effect on a neighbouring cafe, Rí-Rá, which has resumed using single-use cups as well as reusables.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Byrne is confident the scheme will continue to expand with help from community leaders and schools. “We can&#39;t save the world but each of us can make a little change.”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 14 Oct 2023 23:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Ring of fire’ eclipse expected to obscure the sun across parts of the US and Mexico – live updates]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/science/live/2023/oct/14/how-watch-solar-eclipse-annular-what-time-path-live-updates]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T15:19:21Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/76ed9ff7ef9c0ce146d79f094fd926d241912b16/0_232_3500_2101/master/3500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=7b96445a6c76ba9fa3f2dfa4d210fefc&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Partial solar eclipse&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 14 Oct 2023 23:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Wales v Argentina: Rugby World Cup 2023 quarter-final – live]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2023/oct/14/wales-v-argentina-rugby-world-cup-quarter-final-live-score-updates]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T14:49:56Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/18c9e392efa52389fdaca5437eff6223c7704a38/0_542_5176_3105/master/5176.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=bbdcce1420089b864ef85bd999833ca2&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Wales fans dressed as The Beatles enjoy a laugh before the game&lt;/div>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 14 Oct 2023 22:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Louvre in Paris evacuates staff and visitors after receiving written threat]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/14/louvre-in-paris-evacuates-staff-and-visitors-after-receiving-written-threat]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T13:25:43Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/36844117ab3498aff0337564126dfb8399b12573/0_101_3541_2125/master/3541.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=5b1c8bc49a2dffe7a404cdc5c701b9da&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Police cordon at the Louvre&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Thousands of visitors have been evacuated from the Louvre in Paris after museum staff received a written threat.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The warning on Saturday came as France is on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/13/france-on-high-alert-after-suspected-radical-islamist-kills-teacher&quot;>;its highest alert for terrorist attacks&lt;/a>; after the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/13/teacher-killed-in-arras-school-attack-in-northern-france&quot;>;killing of a teacher by a suspected radical Islamist&lt;/a>; in the north of the country on Friday.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The museum said it would remain closed all afternoon “for security reasons” and that police and staff were carrying out “verifications” of the buildings after an estimated 15,000 people were instructed to leave.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Louvre officials said they had received a written message on Saturday morning “stating there is a risk to the museum and its visitors”. They said it had “chosen to evacuate and close for the day in order to carry out essential checks”, adding that those who had booked tickets to visit will be reimbursed.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As many as 7,000 troops are being deployed across the country as the terror threat was raised this weekend. Dominique Bernard, 57, a French literature teacher, was stabbed to death in the courtyard of the Gambetta-Carnot secondary school in Arras on Friday morning. Three other members of staff were injured, two of them critically. Bernard, a father of three, had taught at the school since the 1980s.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A 20-year-old former pupil named as Mohammed M, who was born in Russia&#39;s mainly Muslim North Caucusus, was arrested and is being questioned by anti-terrorist police. He had been put on France&#39;s Fiche S security list as a suspected radical Islamist and was under close surveillance, including phone taps. Police had stopped and searched him on Thursday, but found no reason to detain him.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Louvre, the largest museum in the world and home to Leonardo da Vinci&#39;s Mona Lisa, the Venus de Milo statue and many other internationally recognised masterpieces, has up to 40,000 visitors a day.&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 14 Oct 2023 21:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Germany invites UK to reach improved Brexit trading deal]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/oct/14/germany-invites-uk-to-reach-improved-brexit-trading-deal]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-14T09:31:38Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ef931220e6c8cf90c284d3e76f29b44d8ec076f/119_0_7709_4625/master/7709.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=43f33dc26302a69b8133b865e5437ac6&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Christian Lindner&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;The German finance minister has issued an open invitation to the UK to reach a new deal to improve Brexit trading relations that would reduce trade barriers and “obstacles in daily business life”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Christian Lindner told the BBC: “This is a standing invitation for the UK: if you want to intensify your trade relationship to the EU, call us. We really appreciate the United Kingdom and its values, its people … and I would really, really appreciate it if we can intensify [the trade relationship] again.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;His comments will come as a surprise to the European Commission vice-president, Maroš Šefčovič, who negotiated the Brexit trade deal, and they throw the door open to the Labour leader, Keir Starmer, who has said he will seek “a much better” relationship with the EU if he wins the next general election.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/sep/08/germany-backs-tariff-delay-on-electric-vehicle-sales-uk-and-eu-brexit&quot;>;Germany backs tariff delay on electric vehicle sales between UK and EU&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Šefčovič has insisted the Brexit deal will not be “put in the shredder”. He is also resisting calls from the car industry in the UK and the EU for a three-year suspension of tariffs, scheduled to come into force in January, on electric car exports.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;It is understood he may, however, agree to a one-year suspension as a compromise.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Lindner said Brexit had created “obstacles in daily business life” and was making trade with the UK more difficult.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“In the daily life of German corporates, there are new obstacles since Brexit … I don&#39;t think [the] United Kingdom is benefiting from Brexit,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Experts have said that even without a root and branch review of the Brexit deal, there are ways to reduce barriers.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The UK&#39;s House of Lords &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/apr/29/lords-committee-urges-end-to-brexit-barriers-for-musicians-and-young-people&quot;>;identified 72 areas&lt;/a>; where improvements could be made earlier this year, including easier visa arrangements for touring musicians and theatre performers, a return to the mutual recognition of qualifications for professionals, such as accountants, and a loosening of the rules for visiting schoolchildren.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Lindner&#39;s comments are the first from one of the EU&#39;s biggest economies to suggest the Brexit deal negotiated by Boris Johnson and David Frost is also hurting EU businesses.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;There have been fears that the German economy has moved &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/06/is-germanys-great-economy-sinking-into-slowcession&quot;>;into a “slowcession”&lt;/a>;, with expectations that it will have shrunk by 0.4% this year as result of high inflation, high energy prices and weak international trade.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The government had predicted growth of 0.4% for 2023 in its April forecast, but weakness in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.reuters.com/markets/europe/german-industrial-orders-post-monthly-rise-august-2023-10-06/&quot;>;industrial&lt;/a>; sector and the highest interest rates in a decade are spurring fears of another recession this year in the eurozone&#39;s largest economy.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Germany is the UK&#39;s second-largest trading partner, according to UK government statistics released in September, accounting for 8% of total UK trade.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The daily cost of doing trade has changed, however, with customs and standards paperwork and certification needed after the UK left the single market.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The car industry has &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/sep/22/we-cant-alter-brexit-deal-to-appease-car-industry-says-european-commissioner&quot;>;called for a three-year suspension&lt;/a>; of the pending tariff, but the EU is split. Its commissioner responsible for the internal market, Thierry Breton, recently told the Guardian it could not offer special protection for one industry over another.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Critics say the car industry is to blame, not the Brexit deal, for not accelerating the production of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/sep/23/the-east-german-town-at-the-centre-of-the-new-gold-rush-for-lithium&quot;>;chemicals needed to make electric motor batteries&lt;/a>; and allowing Chinese rivals to steal a march on it.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A UK government spokesperson said: “The trade and cooperation agreement is the world&#39;s largest zero-tariff, zero-quota free trade deal.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It secures the UK market access across key service sectors and opens new opportunities for UK businesses across the globe.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Following the Windsor framework, both the UK and EU have publicly committed to maximising the opportunities of the TCA even further.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 14 Oct 2023 20:22:02 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>